{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858538448,"sessionID":"ses_2869746a0ffei7GouYeMisObog","part":{"id":"prt_d796ad7a0001HQ7mmcxHvJG1jk","messageID":"msg_d7969c713001arKM7DDCV0CnL1","sessionID":"ses_2869746a0ffei7GouYeMisObog","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-0a708ab96b71425284e5acb0cb2316e7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md","content":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Valkey storage backend for AgentCube session management, completing the `valkeyStore` implementation from its current stub state to a fully functional `Store` interface implementation. This provides an open-source, LF-supported Redis-compatible storage alternative with identical data model semantics.\n\n**Current State**: The `valkeyStore` struct exists but all methods return `\"store: valkey not configured\"` errors. The `newValkeyStore` function creates an uninitialized store without actual Valkey client connection.\n\n**Target State**: Fully functional `valkeyStore` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client, supporting all Store interface operations with ZSET-based expiry/activity indexes.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Complete `valkeyStore` implementation with actual Valkey client |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Update `newValkeyStore` to initialize client from options |\n| `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Valkey-specific unit tests (mocked via miniredis or valkey-go mock) |\n\n### Implementation Details\n\n#### valkeyStore struct\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n- `cli`: `valkey.Client` from `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n- Key constants identical to Redis: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n\n#### Method Implementations\n\n| Method | Valkey API |\n|--------|------------|\n| `Ping` | `cli.Do(ctx, B().Ping().Build())` → check for `\"PONG\"` |\n| `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound` |\n| `StoreSandbox` | `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)` with SETNX + 2× ZADD |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | SET with XX flag; check `resp.ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti` with DEL + 2× ZREM |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(key).Min(\"-inf\").Max(score).Limit(0, limit)` → pipeline GET or MGET |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same pattern on `last_activity` key |\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `B().Exists().Key(key)` → int64 == 1; then ZADD |\n| `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\nfunc newValkeyStore(opts *valkeyClientOption) (Store, error) {\n    clientOpts := valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress: opts.InitAddress,\n        Password:    opts.Password,\n    }\n    if opts.DisableCache {\n        clientOpts.DisableCache = true\n    }\n    if opts.ForceSingleClient {\n        clientOpts.ForceSingleClient = true\n    }\n    \n    cli, err := valkey.NewClient(clientOpts)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    return &valkeyStore{\n        cli:                  cli,\n        sessionPrefix:        defaultSessionPrefix,\n        expiryIndexKey:       defaultExpiryIndexKey,\n        lastActivityIndexKey: defaultLastActivityIndexKey,\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Notes |\n|----------|----------|--------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated → `InitAddress` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` → `DisableCache: true` |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` → `ForceSingleClient: true` |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Redis implementation changes (AR-013)\n- Store interface modifications\n- Valkey Cluster TLS configuration\n- Data migration between Redis and Valkey\n- Connection pool tuning\n- Retry/backoff logic beyond valkey-go defaults\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Impact |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Latest | Primary client library; provides `Client`, `ClientOption`, builder API (`B()`) |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Existing | Logging for connection errors |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Existing | `SandboxInfo` struct for JSON marshaling |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Method Usage |\n|----------|--------------|\n| Session Manager | `StoreSandbox`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `UpdateSandbox` |\n| Router | `GetSandboxBySessionID` for session routing |\n| Garbage Collector | `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n| Heartbeat | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Behavior Change**: Current stub returns errors; functional implementation will actually work\n- **No Interface Changes**: Store interface unchanged; existing consumers unaffected\n- **Singleton Behavior**: `STORE_TYPE=valkey` will now produce working store instead of stub\n- **Key Semantics**: Same key patterns as Redis; switching providers preserves data compatibility\n\n### Compatibility Notes\n\n1. **Redis-Valkey Interop**: Same wire protocol; data stored by Redis readable by Valkey\n2. **Valkey MGET Slots**: Comment in design.md notes keys should be in same slot; deployment must ensure consistent hashing\n3. **Error Mapping**: `valkey.IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` (matches Redis `redis.Nil` handling)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use go-redis for Both Providers\n\n**Approach**: Keep single Redis client library; Valkey config just changes address.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Less code; one dependency; Valkey is Redis-compatible |\n| Cons | Loses Valkey-specific optimizations (caching, pipelining); go-redis may lag behind Valkey features |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Valkey-go provides optimized client with built-in caching (`DisableCache` option) and better Valkey-specific support. Dual libraries maintain provider flexibility.\n\n### Alternative 2: Shared Implementation Base\n\n**Approach**: Create abstract `kvStore` struct with common logic; Redis and Valkey wrap it.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Reduces code duplication; unified ZSET logic |\n| Cons | Different client APIs (go-redis vs valkey-go builders); abstraction adds complexity for ~200 lines each |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Go-redis uses method chaining (`ZAdd(ctx, key, Z{...})`) while valkey-go uses builder pattern (`B().Zadd().Key(k).ScoreMember(...).Build()`). Abstraction layer would be more complex than separate implementations.\n\n### Alternative 3: Single Provider Only\n\n**Approach**: Remove Valkey option; only Redis supported.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler maintenance; one client library; fewer tests |\n| Cons | Locks into Redis ecosystem; no open-source LF-supported alternative; limits deployment options |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Valkey is Linux Foundation project as Redis fork; providing both options gives users vendor choice without significant overhead (same data model, same interface).\n\n### Alternative 4: Etcd as Alternative Backend\n\n**Approach**: Add Etcd as third storage backend option.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Kubernetes-native; strong consistency; lease-based expiry |\n| Cons | Higher latency; heavier resource footprint; no native ZSET equivalent |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Session storage needs low-latency key-value with time-based range queries. Sorted sets are optimal; Etcd would require custom index implementation.\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Valkey connection failure on init | Environment validation in `newValkeyStoreFromEnv`; return error before singleton assignment |\n| Client initialization error | `valkey.NewClient` may fail; propagate error to `initStore` → klog.Error |\n| MGET slot requirement | Add documentation note; deployment guide for consistent hashing |\n| Pipeline vs DoMulti semantics | `DoMulti` fails on any error; matches Redis pipeline behavior |\n| Builder pattern confusion | Use consistent `B().Command().Key().Build()` pattern; reference design.md |\n| Missing password validation | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` must be case-insensitive `\"false\"` |\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n1. **Client Initialization**\n   - Import `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n   - `newValkeyStore` creates actual `valkey.Client` from `ClientOption`\n   - Remove singleton pattern inside `newValkeyStore` (use simple constructor)\n\n2. **Ping Implementation**\n   - `cli.Do(ctx, B().Ping().Build())`\n   - Verify response equals `\"PONG\"`\n\n3. **GetSandboxBySessionID**\n   - `B().Get().Key(sessionKey).Build()`\n   - `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → return `ErrNotFound`\n   - Unmarshal JSON bytes to `SandboxInfo`\n\n4. **StoreSandbox**\n   - Validate nil sandbox, zero `ExpiresAt`, empty `SessionID`\n   - Build SETNX command, 2 ZADD commands\n   - `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n   - Check SETNX success (first resp `ToString() != \"OK\"` means already exists → `ErrSessionExists`)\n\n5. **UpdateSandbox**\n   - SET with XX flag via builder\n   - Success: `resp.ToString() == \"OK\"`\n   - Failure: `ErrKeyNotExists`\n\n6. **DeleteSandboxBySessionID**\n   - DoMulti: DEL + 2× ZREM\n\n7. **ListExpiredSandboxes / ListInactiveSandboxes**\n   - `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(indexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(before.Unix()).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n   - Parse session IDs from response\n   - Build keys; use MGET for batch retrieval\n   - Skip missing keys (tolerate `IsValkeyNil`)\n   - Unmarshal valid entries\n\n8. **UpdateSessionLastActivity**\n   - `B().Exists().Key(sessionKey).Build()` → int64 == 1\n   - If missing → `ErrNotFound`\n   - `B().Zadd().Key(lastActivityKey).ScoreMember(score, sessionID).Build()`\n\n9. **Close**\n   - `cli.Close()`; return nil\n\n10. **Tests**\n    - Use miniredis (Redis-compatible mock) for functional tests\n    - Or use valkey-go's mock capabilities\n    - Test all methods; mirror Redis test patterns\n\n## References\n\n- `session-store/design.md` — Valkey implementation specification (lines 395-452)\n- `session-store/spec.md` — Requirements: Valkey environment, ZSET semantics\n- `changes/AR-013/proposal.md` — Redis implementation reference\n- `pkg/store/store_redis.go` — Redis implementation pattern to follow\n- [valkey-go documentation](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go)\n- [Valkey project](https://valkey.io/)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":242,"character":20},"end":{"line":242,"character":39}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/deprecated"},"source":"deprecated","message":"s.cli.ZRangeByScore is deprecated: Use ZRangeArgs with ByScore option instead as of Redis 6.2.0.","tags":[2]},{"range":{"start":{"line":263,"character":20},"end":{"line":263,"character":39}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/deprecated"},"source":"deprecated","message":"s.cli.ZRangeByScore is deprecated: Use ZRangeArgs with ByScore option instead as of Redis 6.2.0.","tags":[2]},{"range":{"start":{"line":386,"character":20},"end":{"line":386,"character":44}},"severity":3,"code":"unusedparams","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedparams#unusedparams"},"source":"unusedparams","message":"unused p